Returns: the priority of the renderer at exit. Value is @B_android#webkit#WebView#RENDERER_PRIORITY_WAIVED_E@, @B_android#webkit#WebView#RENDERER_PRIORITY_BOUND_E@, or @B_android#webkit#WebView#RENDERER_PRIORITY_IMPORTANT_E@
rendererPriorityAtExit().Description: Returns the renderer priority that was set at the time that the renderer exited. This may be greater than the priority that any individual @B_android#webkit#WebView_E@ requested using @B_android#webkit#WebView#setRendererPriorityPolicy_E@.

Returns: true if render process crashed, otherwise it was killed by system.
didCrash().Description: Indicates whether the render process was observed to crash, or whether it was killed by the system. If the render process was killed, this is most likely caused by the system being low on memory.

RenderProcessGoneDetail().Description: This class should not be constructed by applications.

ClassDesc: This class provides more specific information about why the render process exited. The application may use this to decide how to handle the situation. * @apiSince 26
